cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a Mobile Ad-hoc NETwork (MANET) and the flooding time of messages in such a network. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper involves n agents moving in a network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the upper bound on the flooding time and the efficiency of data exchange in the network. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as the paper deals with the spatial probability distribution of agents in the network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) could also be relevant as the paper involves the exchange of data between agents in the network.
